When to Use Which?
Use NAS when:
You need simple file sharing and collaboration among users.
You have a limited budget and want to use existing Ethernet cables.
You are setting up an active archive for unstructured data like photos or backups.
Use SAN when:
You need ultra-low latency for high-traffic databases or e-commerce platforms.
You are running a large virtualized environment (e.g., hundreds of Virtual Machines).
You need massive scalability without putting a heavy load on your main office network.
